name: Turquoise-tinted plumes in the Large Magellanic Cloud
description:
This image shows part of the Large Magellanic Cloud (LMC), a small nearby galaxy that orbits our galaxy, the Milky Way, and appears as a blurred blob in our skies. 

Name:	Large Magellanic Cloud
Type:	Local Universe : Galaxy : Type : Irregular
Distance:	150000 light years
Constellation:	Dorado
Category:	Galaxies

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.
